TITLE: Configuring Filters - Logstash Filter
DESCRIPTION: This snippet configures Logstash to read from stdin, apply grok and date filters, and output to Elasticsearch and stdout. It uses grok to parse the message field according to the COMBINEDAPACHELOG pattern and the date filter to parse a timestamp.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/logstash/blob/main/docs/reference/config-examples.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: ruby
CODE:
```
input { stdin { } }

filter {
  grok {
    match => { "message" => "%{
COMBINEDAPACHELOG}" }
  }
  date {
    match => [ "timestamp" , "dd/MMM/yyyy:HH:mm:ss Z" ]
  }
}

output {
  elasticsearch { hosts => ["localhost:9200"] }
  stdout { codec => rubydebug }
}
```

