TITLE: Referencing Keystore Keys in Logstash Configuration
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to reference values stored in the Logstash keystore within Logstash configuration files and `logstash.yml`. The key is enclosed in `${}` syntax.  It requires that the key-value pair is already stored in the keystore.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/logstash/blob/main/docs/reference/keystore.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
output { elasticsearch {...password => "${ES_PWD}" } } } 
```

