TITLE: Running Logstash with Config File
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to run Logstash with a specific pipeline configuration file using the -f flag. This loads the configuration from the specified file.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/logstash/blob/main/docs/reference/running-logstash-command-line.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
bin/logstash -f mypipeline.conf
```

