TITLE: Starting Logstash with a Custom Pipeline Configuration - Shell
DESCRIPTION: This shell command launches Logstash while specifying a configuration file to define pipeline input and output logic. Replace `mypipeline.conf` with the actual configuration filename. Prerequisites include having the referenced configuration file on the filesystem and Logstash properly installed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/logstash/blob/main/docs/reference/use-filebeat-modules-kafka.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
bin/logstash -f mypipeline.conf
```

