TITLE: Running Logstash with Pipeline Configuration
DESCRIPTION: This shell script demonstrates how to run a Logstash Docker container with a bind-mounted volume for pipeline configuration. It mounts the local directory '~/pipeline/' to '/usr/share/logstash/pipeline/' inside the container. Any configuration files placed in the host's '~/pipeline/' directory will be used by Logstash. The command pulls the image from Docker Hub and runs it with the specified volume mapping.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/logstash/blob/main/docs/reference/docker-config.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
docker run --rm -it -v ~/pipeline/:/usr/share/logstash/pipeline/ docker.elastic.co/logstash/logstash:9.0.0
```

