TITLE: Configuration Parameter Syntax for Logstash Plugins in Ruby
DESCRIPTION: Shows the syntax for defining configuration parameters in Logstash plugins, including validation types, defaults, and other available options.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/logstash/blob/main/docs/extend/input-new-plugin.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: ruby
CODE:
```
config :variable_name, :validate => :variable_type, :default => "Default value", :required => boolean, :deprecated => boolean, :obsolete => string
```

