TITLE: Configuring Logstash Multiline Codec for Java Stack Traces (JSON)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to configure the Logstash `multiline` codec within the `stdin` input plugin to consolidate Java stack traces into single events. It matches lines starting with whitespace (`^\s`) using the `pattern` option and merges them with the previous line using `what => "previous"`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/logstash/blob/main/docs/reference/multiline.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
input {
  stdin {
    codec => multiline {
      pattern => "^\s"
      what => "previous"
    }
  }
}
```

