TITLE: Processing Logs with Conditionals - Logstash Configuration
DESCRIPTION: This Logstash configuration uses conditionals to label events based on the path and apply grok and date filters to access logs.  It includes an 'else if' and an 'else' block to cover other log file types, and outputs the processed data to Elasticsearch and stdout.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/logstash/blob/main/docs/reference/config-examples.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: ruby
CODE:
```
input {
  file {
    path => "/tmp/*_log"
  }
}

filter {
  if [path] =~ "access" {
    mutate { replace => { type => "apache_access" } }
    grok {
      match => { "message" => "%{
COMBINEDAPACHELOG}" }
    }
