TITLE: Translate Field Value - Logstash
DESCRIPTION: This snippet configures the `translate` filter to replace the value of the `response_code` field with a descriptive string, based on a mapping defined in the `dictionary`. It then removes the original `response_code` field. It uses a hash to map the response codes to corresponding descriptions. Requires only the `translate` filter to be installed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/logstash/blob/main/docs/reference/lookup-enrichment.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
filter {
  translate {
    field => "response_code"
    destination => "http_response"
    dictionary => {
      "200" => "OK"
      "403" => "Forbidden"
      "404" => "Not Found"
      "408" => "Request Timeout"
    }
    remove_field => "response_code"
  }
}
```

