TITLE: Configuring Paquet Task in Rakefile (Ruby)
DESCRIPTION: This Rakefile configuration demonstrates how to set up and use the Paquet::Task. It defines a target directory for storing bundled dependencies and uses the `pack` method to specify gems to include (e.g., 'manticore', 'logstash-output-elasticsearch') and the `ignore` method for gems that should be excluded, assuming they are provided by the target system (e.g., 'logstash-core').
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/logstash/blob/main/tools/paquet/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: ruby
CODE:
```
require "paquet"

TARGET_DIRECTORY = File.join(File.dirname(__FILE__), "dependencies")

Paquet::Task.new(TARGET_DIRECTORY) do
  pack "manticore"
  pack "launchy"
  pack "gemoji"
  pack "logstash-output-elasticsearch"

  # Everything not defined here will be assumed to be provided
  # by the target installation
  ignore "logstash-core-plugin-api"
  ignore "logstash-core"
end
```

