TITLE: Checking Package Installation Status on Debian - Ruby
DESCRIPTION: Defines a Ruby method to determine if a package is installed on a Debian system using dpkg and sudo via a helper function. The installed? method executes a shell command to retrieve package information and checks the output for confirmation of installation status. Dependencies include the existence of a sudo_exec! helper and correct permissions. The method expects a package name and returns true if the package is present, otherwise false.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/logstash/blob/main/qa/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Ruby
CODE:
```
def installed?(package)
  stdout = ""
  cmd = sudo_exec!("dpkg -s #{package}")
  stdout = cmd.stdout
  stdout.match(/^Package: #{package}$/)
  stdout.match(/^Status: install ok installed$/)
end
```

