TITLE: Example Usage of 'offline' with nc and host (Shell)
DESCRIPTION: Provides concrete examples comparing normal execution with execution via the 'offline' utility. It shows how attempts to connect using 'nc' or resolve a hostname using 'host' normally might succeed or fail due to network state, but consistently fail with permission errors when run via './offline', demonstrating the network restriction imposed by seccomp.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/logstash/blob/main/qa/integration/fixtures/offline_wrapper/README.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Shell
CODE:
```
% nc localhost 10000
Ncat: Connection refused.

% ./offline nc localhost 10000
Ncat: Permission denied.

% ./offline host google.com
host: isc_socket_bind: permission denied
```

