TITLE: Setting File Path with Environment Variable (Ruby)
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use an environment variable to dynamically set a file path. The `add_field` directive of a `mutate` filter is used to set `my_path` based on the value of the `HOME` environment variable.  This allows for configuration that adapts to the user's home directory.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/logstash/blob/main/docs/reference/environment-variables.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: ruby
CODE:
```
filter {
  mutate {
    add_field => {
      "my_path" => "${HOME}/file.log"
    }
  }
}
```

