TITLE: Configuring CSV Filter for Data Parsing in Logstash
DESCRIPTION: This snippet sets up the CSV filter to parse comma-separated values into individual fields, either using default column names or specified column headers. It allows customization of the separator and field names, and is used to extract structured data from CSV inputs. Dependencies include the CSV filter plugin.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/logstash/blob/main/docs/reference/data-deserialization.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
filter {
  csv {
    separator => ","
    columns => [ "Transaction Number", "Date", "Description", "Amount Debit", "Amount Credit", "Balance" ]
  }
}
...
```

