TITLE: Output Conditional Example - Logstash Output
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the use of conditionals within the output section of a Logstash configuration. It routes events to different outputs (nagios, Elasticsearch, and statsd) based on the 'type' and 'status' fields.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/logstash/blob/main/docs/reference/config-examples.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
output {
  if [type] == "apache" {
    if [status] =~ /^5\d\d/ {
      nagios { ...  }
    } else if [status] =~ /^4\d\d/ {
      elasticsearch { ... }
    }
    statsd { increment => "apache.%{status}" }
  }
}
```
